Singer Teni has bagged an endorsement deal with global electronics company Samsung. The South Korean company is one of the world’s largest producers of electronic devices. Announcing the news, the “Billionaire” hit singer shared an excerpt from what seemed like an advert shoot and wrote: “Newest member of the Samsung family! @samsung #TeamGalaxy.” Samsung Nigeria confirmed the news and shared the same video while welcoming the entertainer to their fold. It tweeted “Introducing the latest member of #TeamGalaxy. Welcome @tenientertainer #SamsungxTeni.” - Advertisement - Congratulatory messages have since continued to pour in from the electronics company, celebrities, fans and followers of Teni Makanaki. Samsung Nigeria said: “Welcome to #TeamGalaxy.”   Woli Agba laments hike in fish price     Davido amused over PA’s proposed O2 welcome speech     PSG star Neymar attends The Batman premiere   Ebuka Obi Uchendu wrote: “Welcome partner.” Broad Shaggi stated: “Congratulations.” tenientertainerworld said: “Congratulations Makanaki. I am proud of you.” Seyi Vibez wrote: “Congrats.” kabiyesijigilola stated: “More wins more life more wealth.” officiallelo said: “Congrats big Superstar.” whilzznwaa wrote: “Congrat the Queen.” everylabelofficials stated: “Congrats!”